The paper deals with the connection between self-assembly and computation, and specifically focuses on the relationship between the size of the smallest self-assembly program and the shape's Kolmogorov complexity. This suggests that the paper is likely to fall under the categories of theoretical computer science (cs.CC, cs.DM, cs.THEORY), computational geometry (cs.CG), and possibly machine learning (cs.LG) due to the use of a universal constructor and the consideration of functions from bit strings to shapes.
